quran[40]{c,v,t}:
  19,59,"Then they were succeeded by a generation who neglected prayer and followed base desires. So they shall meet [the reward of] error"
  19,60,"save for those who repent and believe and work righteousness. It is they who shall enter the Garden, and they shall not be wronged in the least"
  19,61,"Gardens of Eden, those which the Compassionate promised His servants in the Unseen. Verily His Promise shall come to pass"
  19,62,"They shall hear no idle talk therein, but only “Peace!” And therein they shall have their provision, morning and evening"
  19,63,This is the Garden We shall bequeath unto those among Our servants who were reverent
  19,64,"“We descend not, save by the Command of thy Lord. Unto Him belongs that which is before us and that which is behind us, and whatsoever lies between that, and thy Lord is not forgetful—"
  19,65,the Lord of the heavens and the earth and whatsoever is between them. So worship Him and be steadfast in His worship. Dost thou know any who can be named alongside Him?”
  19,66,"Man says, “When I am dead, shall I be brought forth alive?”"
  19,67,"Does man not remember that We created him before, when he was naught"
  19,68,"And by thy Lord, We shall surely gather them and the satans, and We shall surely bring them around Hell on their knees"
  19,69,Then indeed We shall pluck out from every group whosoever among them was most insolent toward the Compassionate
  19,70,Then We shall surely know those who most deserve to burn therein
  19,71,"And there is not one of you, but that he will approach it. It is, with thy Lord, a decree determined"
  19,72,"Then We shall save those who are reverent and leave the wrongdoers therein, on their knees"
  19,73,"And when Our signs are recited unto them as clear proofs, those who disbelieve say unto those who believe, “Which of the two groups is better in station or fairer in company?”"
  19,74,"How many a generation We destroyed before them who were fairer in [their] furnishings and in outward appearance"
  19,75,"Say, “Whosoever is in error, the Compassionate will extend his term till, when they see that which they have been promised, be it the punishment or the Hour, they will know whose position is worse, and whose host is weaker.”"
  19,76,"God increases in guidance those who are rightly guided. And that which endures—righteous deeds—are better in reward with thy Lord, and better in return"
  19,77,"Hast thou not considered the one who disbelieves in Our signs, and says, “I shall be given wealth and children.”"
  19,78,"Has he penetrated the Unseen, or made a pact with the Compassionate"
  19,79,"Nay, but We shall record that which he says, and We shall prolong for him the punishment"
  19,80,"And We shall inherit from him that which he claims, and he will come unto Us alone"
  19,81,"And they have taken gods apart from God, that they might be a strength for them"
  19,82,"Nay, but they will disavow their worship, and they will become an opponent unto them"
  19,83,"Hast thou not considered how We unleash the satans on the disbelievers, to incite them cunningly"
  19,84,So hasten not against them; verily We are counting for them a number
  19,85,On the Day We shall gather the reverent to the Compassionate as an honored delegation
  19,86,and We shall drive the guilty into Hell as a thirsty herd
  19,87,"They have no power of intercession, save the one who has made a pact with the Compassionate"
  19,88,"And they say, “The Compassionate has taken a child.”"
  19,89,You have indeed asserted a terrible thing
  19,90,"The heavens are well-nigh rent thereby, and the earth split asunder, and the mountains made to fall down in ruins"
  19,91,that they should claim for the Compassionate a child
  19,92,It is not fitting for the Compassionate to take a child
  19,93,"There is none in the heavens and on the earth, but that it comes unto the Compassionate as a servant"
  19,94,"He has taken account of them, and numbered them exactly"
  19,95,"And each of them shall come unto Him on the Day of Resurrection, alone"
  19,96,"Surely those who believe and perform righteous deeds, for them shall the Compassionate ordain love"
  19,97,"We have only made this easy upon thy tongue that thou mayest give glad tidings unto the reverent thereby, and that thereby thou mayest warn a contentious people"
  19,98,"How many a generation before them have We destroyed? Dost thou perceive even one of them, or hear from them a murmur"